text: YWCA-YMCA of Sweden () is the Sweden-branch of YMCA and YWCA. It was established in 1966 when YMCA of Sweden and YWCA of Sweden merged. In 2011 the organization decided to use the term "KFUM" in promotion with "M" standing for "människor" ("people"). Earlier the "m" stood for "män" (men)Protokoll – 1(13) YWCA-YMCA of Sweden's national meeting in Umeå, 29-30 October 2011 . accessdate: 5 March 2012. YWCA-YMCA of Sweden has 60 000 members. It has 4 000 local associations. Several Swedish YWCA-YMCA associations have been successful in sports. ==References== ==Other websites== *official website Category:1966 establishments in Sweden Category:Christianity in Sweden Category:Organizations based in Stockholm
